\\"></TD><TD></TD><TD COLSPAN=\\\"13\\\"><TABLE CELLSPACING=\\\"0\\\" CELLPADDING=\\\"0\\\" LANG=\\\"en-US\\\" style=\\\"\\\"><TR><TD style=\\\"WIDTH:113.79mm;min-width: 113.79mm;HEIGHT:4.06mm;\\\" class=\\\"a48l\\\">Subject: Storage Critical Day, Effective February 22, 2026 - Op Areas 1, 2, 4, 10</TD></TR></TABLE></TD><TD></TD><TD COLSPAN=\\\"5\\\"><TABLE CELLSPACING=\\\"0\\\" CELLPADDING=\\\"0\\\" LANG=\\\"en-US\\\" style=\\\"\\\"><TR><TD style=\\\"WIDTH:56.78mm;min-width: 56.78mm;HEIGHT:3.97mm;\\\" class=\\\"a51l\\\">Author: Jon Young</TD></TR></TABLE></TD><TD ROWSPAN=\\\"4\\\" COLSPAN=\\\"2\\\"></TD></TR><TR><TD style=\\\"HEIGHT:4.06mm;WIDTH:0.00mm\\\"></TD><TD COLSPAN=\\\"20\\\"></TD></TR><TR VALIGN=\\\"top\\\"><TD style=\\\"HEIGHT:4.06mm;WIDTH:0.00mm\\\"></TD><TD></TD><TD COLSPAN=\\\"5\\\"><TABLE CELLSPACING=\\\"0\\\" CELLPADDING=\\\"0\\\" LANG=\\\"en-US\\\" style=\\\"\\\"><TR><TD style=\\\"WIDTH:42.67mm;min-width: 42.67mm;HEIGHT:4.06mm;\\\" class=\\\"a24\\\">Notice Text</TD></TR></TABLE></TD><TD ROWSPAN=\\\"2\\\" COLSPAN=\\\"14\\\"></TD></TR><TR><TD style=\\\"HEIGHT:1.78mm;WIDTH:0.00mm\\\"></TD><TD COLSPAN=\\\"6\\\"></TD></TR><TR VALIGN=\\\"top\\\"><TD style=\\\"HEIGHT:6.35mm;WIDTH:0.00mm\\\"></TD><TD></TD><TD COLSPAN=\\\"21\\\"><TABLE CELLSPACING=\\\"0\\\" CELLPADDING=\\\"0\\\" LANG=\\\"en-US\\\" style=\\\"\\\"><TR><TD style=\\\"WIDTH:195.11mm;min-width: 195.11mm;HEIGHT:6.35mm;\\\" class=\\\"a54 r8\\\"><DIV style=\\\"overflow-x:hidden;WIDTH:193.70mm;\\\"><DIV style=\\\"margin-top:10pt;padding-bottom:10pt;\\\" class=\\\"a53\\\"><span class=\\\"a52\\\">Pursuant to the General Terms &amp; Conditions of TCO&#39;s FERC Gas Tariff, Section 19.7, shippers are advised that due to forecasted colder temperatures and increased market demand beginning Sunday, February 22, 2026, Storage Critical Days are necessary for deliveries to all Market Areas within Operating Areas 1, 2, 4, and 10. Please note the following:</span></DIV><DIV style=\\\"padding-bottom:10pt;\\\" class=\\\"a53\\\"><span style=\\\"font-weight:700;\\\" class=\\\"a52\\\">Storage Critical Days</span><span class=\\\"a52\\\">:&#160; Sunday, February 22, 2026, and continuing until further notice. TCO will monitor conditions and provide updates as necessary.&#160;&#160;</span></DIV><DIV style=\\\"padding-bottom:10pt;\\\" class=\\\"a53\\\"><span style=\\\"font-weight:700;\\\" class=\\\"a52\\\">Applicable Market Areas</span><span class=\\\"a52\\\">:&#160; All Storage Withdrawals delivered to all Market Areas within Operating Areas 1, 2, 4, and 10 (see Market Areas below). &#160;&#160;&#160;</span></DIV><DIV style=\\\"padding-bottom:10pt;\\\" class=\\\"a53\\\"><span style=\\\"font-weight:700;\\\" class=\\\"a52\\\">Applicable Penalties</span><span class=\\\"a52\\\">:&#160; &#160;</span></DIV><DIV style=\\\"padding-bottom:10pt;\\\" class=\\\"a53\\\"><span class=\\\"a52\\\">- FSS MDWQ - Withdrawn quantities in excess of 103% of the applicable contract MDWQ will be assessed a penalty based on a price per Dth equal to three times the midpoint rate for “Columbia Gas, Appalachia,” posted in Gas Daily.&#160;&#160;</span></DIV><DIV style=\\\"padding-bottom:10pt;\\\" class=\\\"a53\\\"><span class=\\\"a52\\\">- FSS SCQ - If withdrawals from storage result in the FSS contract having a negative SCQ balance, a penalty of $5 per Dth will be assessed.&#160;</span></DIV><DIV style=\\\"padding-bottom:10pt;\\\" class=\\\"a53\\\"><span class=\\\"a52\\\">- FSS MMWQ - Monthly Withdrawal Quantities that exceed 30% (February Limit)&#160;of SCQ will be assessed a penalty of $5.00 per Dth. &#160;&#160;</span></DIV><DIV style=\\\"padding-bottom:10pt;\\\" class=\\\"a53\\\"><span style=\\\"font-weight:700;\\\" class=\\\"a52\\\">NOTE</span><span class=\\\"a52\\\">:&#160;&#160;Transporter projects no availability of interruptible storage withdrawal services (SIT, ISS, and FSS/ FSS-M with zero MDSQ) and excess FSS withdrawals with delivery to one of the affected Market Areas.&#160; PAL loans/ unparks with a delivery within the affected Market Areas will not be available. &#160;Due ship nominations will be scheduled to zero.</span></DIV><DIV style=\\\"padding-bottom:10pt;\\\" class=\\\"a53\\\"><span class=\\\"a52\\\">Please contact your Customer Services Representative with any questions. &#160;&#160;</span></DIV><DIV style=\\\"padding-bottom:10pt;\\\" class=\\\"a53\\\"><span style=\\\"font-weight:700;\\\" class=\\\"a52\\\">Op Area 1 - MA 33, 34</span></DIV><DIV style=\\\"padding-bottom:10pt;\\\" class=\\\"a53\\\"><span style=\\\"font-weight:700;\\\" class=\\\"a52\\\">Op Area 2 - MA 20</span></DIV><DIV style=\\\"padding-bottom:10pt;\\\" class=\\\"a53\\\"><span style=\\\"font-weight:700;\\\" class=\\\"a52\\\">Op Area 4 - MA 21, 22, 23, 24, 25, 29</span></DIV><DIV style=\\\"padding-bottom:10pt;\\\" class=\\\"a53\\\"><span style=\\\"font-weight:700;\\\" class=\\\"a52\\\">Op Area 10 - MA 28, 30, 31</span></DIV></DIV></TD></TR></TABLE></TD></TR></TABLE></TD></TR></TABLE></TD></TR></TABLE></DIV></TD><TD WIDTH=\\\"100%\\\" HEIGHT=\\\"0\\\"></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH=\\\"0\\\" HEIGHT=\\\"100%\\\"></TD></TR></TABLE></DIV></DIV></body></html>\"}],\"temperature\":0.1,\"max_tokens\":2000,\"response_format\":{\"type\":\"json_object\"}},\"headers\":{\"Content-Type\":\"application/json\",\"api-key\":\"AwX1mym8WNOwDFipRpDFxrz1bvaIAZJFkHH126iCClxlMtQOH5GUJQQJ99CDACHYHv6XJ3w3AAAAACOGUqcL\"}},\"outputs\":{\"statusCode\":400,\"headers\":{\"x-ms-rai-invoked\":\"true\",\"X-Request-ID\":\"bf622335-db2d-4c62-a178-3d242a6ba4b1\",\"apim-request-id\":\"bf42687e-e656-400b-9a68-ae5029e76f39\",\"Strict-Transport-Security\":\"max-age=31536000; includeSubDomains; preload\",\"x-ms-client-request-id\":\"86c4efb0-2a6a-4b2f-abd9-a5cf026840ec\",\"x-ms-deployment-name\":\"gpt-5.2\",\"X-Content-Type-Options\":\"nosniff\",\"x-ms-region\":\"East US 2\",\"Date\":\"Mon, 20 Apr 2026 17:10:15 GMT\",\"Content-Length\":\"245\",\"Content-Type\":\"application/json\"},\"body\":{\"error\":{\"message\":\"Unsupported para